---
description: Production rules for NewsFlow AI
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `SYSTEM_PROMPT.md` and `NEWSFLOW_AI_PRODUCTION_SPEC.md` before architectural or implementation work.

Mandatory:
- Production code only; no fake UI as completion.
- TypeScript strict mode.
- Backend authorization and workspace isolation.
- Long-running work belongs in workers.
- External integrations use adapters.
- Publishing is human-approved by default and idempotent.
- Facebook tokens are encrypted, never exposed to the browser, and never logged.
- Approved RSS/APIs first; no paywall or anti-bot bypass.
- AI output is untrusted and must pass deterministic verification.
- Preserve factual names, dates, scores, numbers, quotations, and uncertainty.
- Add tests with every critical feature.
- Run lint, typecheck, tests, and build before claiming completion.
- Work only on the requested phase.
- Report exact observed command results.
